{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A request whose signature does not match its body is rejected with 401 and not forwarded.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is handler wiring: signature verification result must gate queue handoff. A single-function Unit test can miss a real bug in module handoff (verifier->handler->queue). Not System: behavior text does not require real network/OS/subprocess; in-process HTTP harness plus queue spy can expose it. No AI/ML dependency.","test_description":"Run the webhook route in-process with real middleware/body parsing config, send a signed request with intentionally mismatched raw body/signature, assert HTTP 401 and assert queue enqueue API was not called.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"An event is written to the persistent queue before HTTP 200 acknowledgment is returned.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is ordering across modules (HTTP handler and persistence layer). Need real local persistence implementation (or test DB/filesystem) to catch ack-before-durable-write bugs. Not System: no real external network/subprocess contract required by behavior text. No AI/ML dependency.","test_description":"Use in-process server + real persistent queue adapter against local test storage. Instrument write completion, send webhook, and assert write commit timestamp/flag occurs before 200 response is observed.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The handler returns the HTTP response without waiting for downstream processing of the event to finish.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure appears in async orchestration between enqueue path and downstream processor trigger. Integratio