tional queue record).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"When the queue reports it is full, the handler returns 503 with a Retry-After header.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is contract mapping between queue-layer 'full' signal and HTTP response composition. Needs module interaction, not just one function. Not System: no required real external infra; queue-full condition can be reproduced in-process. No AI/ML dependency.","test_description":"Run route with queue module configured/stubbed to return a deterministic full-capacity error; assert HTTP 503 and presence/value format of Retry-After header.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.73,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"The persistent queue actually enforces its configured capacity limit and rejects events that would exceed it.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This validates queue component behavior with real local persistence semantics (DB/filesystem state), beyond a pure function. Integration is the minimum to catch configuration/state wiring and persistence-layer enforcement bugs. Not System: behavior text does not require external network/subprocess/OS contracts beyond local storage.","test_description":"Instantiate the real persistent queue against local test storage with a small configured capacity, enqueue up to limit, then attempt one more and assert explicit rejection/error without increasing stored item count.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
